It's fitting that this video's longest segment consists of our hostess quipping about having to pee, poking buttons on an automated toilet, and then pressing her ear to the door while commenting (at great length) on the sounds the toilet made as it cleaned itself. Another useful tip was to go to a luxury designer's off-season store and ask whether the garments for sale were "rejects." The rest consisted of cursory glimpses of monuments, a bit of can-can dancing, and some lessons in embarrassing mispronunciation. If you're at all interested in Paris' art, culture, history, architecture, or any of the many other things that make it one of the great cities of the world, look elsewhere.
Good dvd. Just wish it had a little more info on Oahu, like more hotels, tours & etc.. But still worth viewing for 1st timers to Oahu.
